external_knowledge:
- "Comprehensive review profiles" implies a detailed and structured report; 
- A high average rating suggests a well-regarded product or reviewer; 
- Total reviews count signifies the popularity or the breadth of feedback a product has received; 
- Review types refer to whether the reviews are Positive, Negative, or Neutral, important for understanding the general sentiment around a product beyond just the rating; 
- Average sentiment scores provide a more nuanced measure than just the average rating, capturing the emotional tone of reviews; 
- Reviewer information, including their ID, name, number of reviews, and average rating, helps in assessing the reliability or consistency of reviewers; 
- High reviewer productivity (number of reviews) might imply either diligence or an attempt to game the system; 
- Average reviewer rating is crucial for understanding a reviewer's general attitude towards products.

sql:
SELECT reviewer_name, COUNT(DISTINCT reviewer_location) as unique_location_count
FROM reviewers
GROUP BY reviewer_name;

SELECT AVG(num_reviews) AS avg_reviews_per_reviewer
FROM (
    SELECT reviewer_id, COUNT(review_id) AS num_reviews
    FROM reviews
    GROUP BY reviewer_id
);
